<!--beginarticle-->
<PRE>Granted, but hackers don't work within what the RFC's say, or on the converse can work within exactly what they say to find vulnerabilities. If I don't know or need what type 4 does then I will block it until a time where I do need it or I find it did in fact break something. Why leave it open just because something tells you to? I'd expect an even better network engineer to make their own rules.

Dan. 

